---
description: Find all TODO comments in the repo and group them by file
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: false
---
When the user asks to audit or list pending work, scan the workspace for
`TODO`, `FIXME`, `HACK`, and `XXX` comments and report them grouped by file.

Rules:

- Search source files only — skip `node_modules/`, `.venv/`, `dist/`,
  `build/`, and anything matched by `.gitignore`.
- Case-insensitive match on the marker tokens.
- Strip leading comment characters (`#`, `//`, `/*`, `*`) before showing
  the comment body.
- Group by relative file path; sort matches inside each group by line
  number ascending.
- Format each entry as `L<line>: <comment text>`.
- Finish with a one-line summary: total markers and number of files
  affected.
- If nothing is found, say so plainly. Do not invent matches.
